div.p: Group 1 Mapping from http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/SampledData|5.0.0 to unspecified code system

tr.td: FHIR R5 ComplexType `SampledData` is representable via FHIR R4 extensions. Element `SampledData` has is mapped to FHIR R4 element `SampledData`, but has no comparisons.
Element `SampledData.origin` has is mapped to FHIR R4 element `SampledData.origin`, but has no comparisons.
Element `SampledData.interval` has is mapped to FHIR R4 element `SampledData.period`, but has no comparisons.
Element `SampledData.intervalUnit` has a context of SampledData based on following the parent source element upwards and mapping to `SampledData`.
Element `SampledData.factor` has is mapped to FHIR R4 element `SampledData.factor`, but has no comparisons.
Element `SampledData.lowerLimit` has is mapped to FHIR R4 element `SampledData.lowerLimit`, but has no comparisons.
Element `SampledData.upperLimit` has is mapped to FHIR R4 element `SampledData.upperLimit`, but has no comparisons.
Element `SampledData.dimensions` has is mapped to FHIR R4 element `SampledData.dimensions`, but has no comparisons.

Note that there is an externally-defined extension that has been flagged as the representation of FHIR R5 element `SampledData.codeMap` with an unmapped Canonical type: `http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/alternate-canonical`. Element `SampledData.codeMap` has a context of SampledData based on following the parent source element upwards and mapping to `SampledData`.
Element `SampledData.offsets` has a context of SampledData based on following the parent source element upwards and mapping to `SampledData`.
Element `SampledData.data` has is mapped to FHIR R4 element `SampledData.data`, but has no comparisons.
